1. Install the ldc compiler and tango libraries from this guide:
http://www.dsource.org/projects/ldc/wiki/WikiStart#Ubuntuldcandldcdailypackages

2. Install mysql and development files:
sudo apt-get install mysql-client mysql-server libmysqlclient15-dev python-mysqldb python-pexpect build-essential bzr ldc-daily

3. Download the code:
cd ~
bzr branch lp:native-rest-cannon
cd native-rest-cannon/src

4. Change the site's database user and port
./gen configure database user:root password:password
./gen configure server port:2345

5. Generate, build, run:
./gen create database
./gen migrate
./build
./run

6. In your web browser navigate to http://localhost:2345/users and you should see a basic CRUD example.

7. Now look at the code and start hacking. I will add more formal documentation when things are a little more fleshed out.

